# Villa Rossa Kempinski

A sophisticated, responsive website for a luxury hotel and restaurant. Built with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript ‚Äì no frameworks. Features dynamic offer management via localStorage, a reservation system with form validation, and a clean, consistent UI.

![Homepage Screenshot](screenshot-placeholder.jpg)

## ‚ú® Features

- **Three fully interlinked pages**: Home, Reservations, Admin
- **Semantic HTML5** (`header`, `nav`, `main`, `section`, `footer`)
- **Responsive design** ‚Äì mobile, tablet, desktop with CSS Grid & Flexbox
- **Persistent data** using `localStorage` (offers and reservations)
- **Form validation** with clear error messages
- **Admin panel** to add/delete special offers ‚Äì changes instantly reflect on homepage
- **Reservation system** ‚Äì book a table/room, view your bookings
- **Elegant typography** (Google Fonts: Playfair Display, Montserrat)
- **Font Awesome icons** for enhanced visual feedback

## Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3 (Grid, Flexbox, Media Queries)
- JavaScript (ES6+)
- LocalStorage API
- Git & GitHub

##  How to Run
. Use the navigation menu to explore:
   - **Home** ‚Äì view current offers (populated via Admin)
   - **Reservations** ‚Äì fill the form to book; see all your bookings
   - **Admin** ‚Äì add new offers (title, description, price, image) ‚Äì they will appear on Home

All data is stored in your browser's localStorage ‚Äì no backend required.

